#contacted.hidden
    .ui.container(style="width: 90%;")
        .limit
            #contacted-read
                h1.ui.header.large#learn-title(style="margin-top: 10px;")
                    .content
                        i.book.icon
                        | When being contacted by scammers
            .ui.stackable.grid(style="margin-top: 10px;")
                .eight.wide.column
                    .dosContainer
                        .ui.large.blue.fluid.label
                            i.thumbs.up.icon 
                            | Do's
                        .ui.bulleted.list 
                            .item Always ask yourself “Do I have an account with the company or know the person who is contacting me?” before giving out personal information.
                            .item Look up the company’s phone number and call the company to ask if any request is legitimate and safe.
                            .item Carefully examine spellings in email addresses and URLs to check if there are any minor typos because scammers may try to pose as a legitimate company.
                            .item Check whether the website has secure symbols, like a padlock or key symbol on your status bar.
                .eight.wide.column
                    .dontsContainer
                        .ui.large.red.fluid.label
                            i.thumbs.down.icon 
                            | Don'ts
                        .ui.bulleted.list 
                            .item Don’t share any personal information over the internet and on public computers unless you are sure it’s safe or you initiated the contact
                            .item Don’t give out usernames and passwords
                            .item Don’t click on anything in an unsolicited email or text
                            .item Don’t call a number left on your voicemail by a robocaller or listed in a suspicious email or text
                            .item Don’t download anything you don’t know is safe
                            .item Don’t use websites that start with “http://” instead of “https://” 
                img.ui.centered.fluid.image(src='/images/padlock.svg' style="width: 650px; z-index: -1; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: -10px;" alt="A padlock is a symbol of a secure website")
                .ui.centered.row
                    p(style="line-height: 1.4rem; font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: left; font-style: italic; width: 550px;") A website with a padlock and https is considered secure as it uses encryption to protect your data.
